data.content:
## What Changed

Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0 upgrades to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1**. This is a major object-model overhaul. Here are the breaking changes in your code:

| # | .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) | Why |
|---|-------------------------|--------------------------|-----|
| 1 | `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace (`OpenApiString`, etc.) | Removed — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` (`JsonValue`, `JsonNode`) | v2 uses `JsonNode` for arbitrary values |
| 2 | `param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString(…)` | `param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create(…)` | `Example` is now `JsonNode?` |
| 3 | `new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }` on an `OpenApiSecurityScheme` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")` | Dedicated reference subtypes replace the generic `Reference` + `ReferenceType` pattern |
| 4 | `property.Value.Nullable = false` | `property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` | OpenAPI 3.1 removed `nullable`; nullability is now a flag on the `type` keyword |

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;              // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;  // for OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");          // #1, #2
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2"); // #3
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;     // #4
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Quick summary of the rules going forward

- **`IOpenApiAny` → `JsonNode`** everywhere (examples, extensions, defaults).
- **`ReferenceType` enum + `OpenApiReference`** → purpose-built reference classes in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References` (e.g., `OpenApiSchemaReference`, `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`, `OpenApiParameterReference`).
- **`Nullable` bool** → `JsonSchemaType.Null` flag on `Type` (a `[Flags]` enum).
